reviews.review_text:
Try This On For Size Huge.

Thanks for the work on this.  Sound is fantastic to go along with an amazing show.

Oh, and I'm not complaining about the Zip file.  Wink, wink.

My #1 Wish I was there show I have been listening over and over in awe to the absolute gratitude and love the Brits showered upon GD band at this show. And did the Dead ever play back the love.

Top 5 Ever:  Row Jimmy, Wharf Rat, Eyes of the World, US Blues; multiple encores (just when they inkle " we bid you good night," they launch into yet another encore instead.)

The frenzy over US Blues made me really wonder, since it is chock full of American idioms that the Brits presumably do not know, use, or actually understand. So why all the glee?  Possibly because Capt. Trips himself was having such a great time of it, and he can be infectious that way. 

And you know how people always shout out the songs they want to hear? This one dude shouts "Play Everything!" and then others picked it up. Honest to God, if humanly and legally possible for the dead to hit all 200+ songs in their catalouge that night, there would never have been a more appreciative and deserving audience. IMHO.
en fuego sunshine daydream makes no since ! in a good way tho. the best way

Supreme Show; Supreme Matrix This show is utterly fantastic.  Thank you Jerry, Phil, Bob, Billy, and Ned.

This matrix that Dave Usborne did is exquisite.  Thank you Dave.

Put the two together and you have absolutely can't miss  Desert Island stuff here.  5 stars on show.  5 stars on fidelity.

Beware the Pranksters Extremely sophisticated and generous playing for the time when this audio was taken. To have seen the boys (and girl) play in Europe would effort an entirely new perspective, undoubtably evident here on such a mysterious tape. Needless to say, the music is sincere and perfect for an audience that might not have realized where or what they were attending. My sincerest thanks on this wonderful summer day that's unfolding for me * Nick.
